<subSubSection id="B2A863A09B3599566000E8B36FED6AC6" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="749306B21648954EB1E57BA52063AD6A" pageNumber="41">
The family 
<taxonomicName id="1E892B30059DD62176260B4708F3DF0C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Amphiliidae</taxonomicName>
includes about 66 species of generally small Afro-tropical catfishes, known commonly as mountain catfishes (Skelton 2001) or loach catfishes (Nelson 1994, 2006; Berra 2001). The species are distributed from the Senegal River in the West throughout coastal West Africa, West Central Africa, the Congo basin, the Nile and East African coastal rivers from the Webi-Shebeli to the Mkomaas River system in South Africa (Berra 2001, 
<normalizedToken id="DCC255A45B0228634424AC0D1E3535D4" originalValue="Lévêque">Leveque</normalizedToken>
1997, Skelton 2001). Diogo (2003) provides a recent review and analysis of the anatomy, phylogeny and taxonomy of the 
<taxonomicName id="96EEF5A39819018C710E30CD05F92AA3" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Amphiliidae</taxonomicName>
indicating that there are at least three major lineages that warrant sub-familial status, viz., the 
<taxonomicName id="D43C8EA26627876596A72DE58AAD793B" pageNumber="41" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Amphiliinae">Amphiliinae</taxonomicName>
, the 
<taxonomicName id="40F9B4F9F5409D2AB063DB524FA61914" pageNumber="41" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Leptoglanidinae">Leptoglanidinae</taxonomicName>
, and the 
<taxonomicName id="185EAC52CEF5D353EF32EE9F73605745" pageNumber="41" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Doumeinae">Doumeinae</taxonomicName>
. Diogo’s (2003) account gives detailed character diagnoses of these sub-families.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E79CA456E16A06E2590009A684B87E82" lastPageNumber="43" pageNumber="42">
Amphiliids are small (the largest species reach to about 200 mm SL) benthic riverine catfishes with a wide range of body form from soft-bodied to slender, firm-bodied and highly streamlined forms, some with bony plates along the body. Amphiliid catfishes are poorly known from WCA where representatives of two sub-families, the 
<taxonomicName id="5F13D0BEC7E7BD4F88E89B217010BA2E" pageNumber="42" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Amphiliinae">Amphiliinae</taxonomicName>
and the 
<taxonomicName id="26C1D9B095DF89FE251F4E1949712182" pageNumber="42" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Doumeinae">Doumeinae</taxonomicName>
occur. The 
<taxonomicName id="EAE56170A9600A56DF90651D189A17C5" pageNumber="42" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Amphiliinae">Amphiliinae</taxonomicName>
are more generalized soft-bodied forms with two genera in the WCA region, 
<taxonomicName id="15D49C6A4A05455F16289E570C046E9C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" genus="Amphilius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
Amphilius 
<normalizedToken id="EC04388A19527BFD67E27D6EB7DEF768" originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="FF4B10EC9988B6BAD377184145F970C1" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:EB1AFD4D-9B6D-4D03-9A67-B53999EAAC78" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" genus="Paramphilius" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Paramphilius Pellegrin 1907:23" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Paramphilius Pellegrin</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="2E4F6AE04FEC9E2734D1C371BBA9FCFA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" genus="Amphilius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Amphilius</taxonomicName>
from the WCA include 
<taxonomicName id="A52FB93F47846AD136273BC5BA9D8EC5" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" genus="Amphilius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">A. longirostris (Boulenger, 1901)</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="945E2317F943F9C409D4295D61A3F8E0" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:BAC3CEE9-9BBC-4F7F-81FF-9C3D636F655B" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" genus="Amphilius" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Amphilius pulcher Pellegrin 1929:640" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pulcher">A. pulcher Pellegrin, 1929</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="92AC4AA6DEAF52AD81DD19BA326A8DDB" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:47363F73-A16A-4B41-B358-C4D7C8A73480" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" genus="Amphilius" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Amphilius nigricaudatus Pellegrin 1909:67" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigricaudatus">A. nigricaudatus Pellegrin, 1909</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="DF8F11B633F82C865A314D9F21317CF7" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CFF782B6-14A0-4B44-87B2-53E7BF96D8B0" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" genus="Amphilius" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Amphilius baudoni Pellegrin 1928:453" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="baudoni">Amphilius baudoni Pellegrin, 1928</taxonomicName>
was described from the region but is shown here to be a species of 
<taxonomicName id="FA945838AE833DDACA93F7BB336F590E" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:EB1AFD4D-9B6D-4D03-9A67-B53999EAAC78" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" genus="Paramphilius" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Paramphilius Pellegrin 1907:23" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Paramphilius</taxonomicName>
, a genus that includes three species from West Africa (Skelton et al., 2003) and 
<taxonomicName id="450DF2492CE9659FB545C93452677695" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:1CE23B87-879F-44A8-89F0-A74DB11E01C2" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" genus="Paramphilius" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Paramphilius goodi Harry 1953:203" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="goodi">Paramphilius goodi Harry, 1953</taxonomicName>
from WCA. Four new species of 
<taxonomicName id="A2EC5279A56AF99E075DE8FD36BD0DB8" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" genus="Amphilius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Amphilius</taxonomicName>
are recognized and described in this paper.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4FDAA575D7D4C7771FD2B30391EE4D7D" pageNumber="43">
Doumeine amphiliids are mostly slender and streamlined, well adapted to living in fast flowing currents. Their axial skeleton is progressively modified in the different species forming, in most genera, linear series of bony ridges or ‘plates’ along the body. Modified vertebrae are tightly inter-connected and bear stout bi-lateral dorsal and ventral flanges that, in genera other than 
<taxonomicName id="5D785BF687E29534523ADC2EDACFCD03" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:1148424C-8833-4034-9EDB-303E964EE1DB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" genus="Doumea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Doumea Sauvage 1879:96 [7]" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Doumea Sauvage</taxonomicName>
, expand distally to form linear series of bony plates exposed at the body surface. Two of the five doumeine genera, 
<taxonomicName id="8FDC601545072E6DDA43D83761EE07D9" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:1148424C-8833-4034-9EDB-303E964EE1DB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" genus="Doumea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Doumea Sauvage 1879:96 [7]" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Doumea</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="8D4072DF04B14B07D4D89E4C92F6D25C" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:18BF6D48-6D42-4C45-BB0E-AD0F0B67FD55" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" genus="Phractura" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Phractura Boulenger 1900:527" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Phractura Boulenger</taxonomicName>
, occur in the West Central African region. The known and described 
<taxonomicName id="95E36F531404DC8613FE299687FAF338" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:1148424C-8833-4034-9EDB-303E964EE1DB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" genus="Doumea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Doumea Sauvage 1879:96 [7]" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Doumea</taxonomicName>
from the WCA include 
<taxonomicName id="39206F9F26048EECE262527F53C04EF1" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:DD318F95-2F88-40F6-950E-7AC858150E2D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" genus="Doumea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Doumea typica Sauvage 1879:97 [8]" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="typica">D. typica Sauvage, 1878</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="BCB711C283318A330BA4DDDFA7F65286" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E1C58DFC-DB30-419E-A65F-DDA497253198" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" genus="Doumea" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Doumea thysi Skelton 1989:6" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thysi">D. thysi Skelton, 1989</taxonomicName>
. An additional two species are described herein. Skelton (2007) recognizes four species of 
<taxonomicName id="2B4D58769FA1C15ABE48DEF3BC648A28" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:18BF6D48-6D42-4C45-BB0E-AD0F0B67FD55" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" genus="Phractura" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Phractura Boulenger 1900:527" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Phractura</taxonomicName>
in the WCA region, namely 
<taxonomicName id="3F1DE5779C7F5C021C66C9259C089104" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:DC42BC88-CDA4-48BA-B2F1-E7A0E2FF599D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" genus="Phractura" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Phractura brevicauda Boulenger 1911:502" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brevicauda">P. brevicauda Boulenger, 1911</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="9DE18A177A0E07A59009CEB33D2EC71E" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E9C68935-DFCB-4297-A455-5C218C494EED" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" genus="Phractura" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Phractura longicauda Boulenger 1903:439" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longicauda">P. longicauda Boulenger, 1903</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="1AE76B27FF123D5C3844692209797A46" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F454C517-4B72-4514-83ED-56218D5184A6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Amphiliidae" genus="Phractura" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Phractura gladysae Pellegrin 1931:209" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gladysae">P. gladysae Pellegrin, 1931</taxonomicName>
and one new species as described herein.
</paragraph>
